@maxconi I haven't, would be happy to review a PR contributing this feature :). Do you have any questions about the API proposal above or how the existing autologging integrations for keras/Tensorflow work?

I think my preferred of the options for handling pipelines is 2).

We should also think about how we handle managing active runs - for example in Keras autologging, we'll automatically start *and* end a run when `keras_model.fit()` is called with no active run, as you can see [here](https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/blob/8bc2749b97c2bb05146ed4820c5320dae4ef593d/mlflow/keras.py#L426). I'm not as sure that the same is the right behavior for scikit-learn, looking at [this example](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/plot_isotonic_regression.html#sphx-glr-auto-examples-plot-isotonic-regression-py) which calls `fit` or `fit_transform` on multiple estimators in sequence. However maybe it's a reasonable place to start - but would be curious to hear your thoughts :)
